. How to view the Query Execution Plan?You can use this information to identify the steps the database is taking to execute your query and to make optimizations accordingly.If you're not already using query execution plans to optimize your SQL code, start today!
You can view the query execution plan in most database management systems, such as SQL Server or MySQL. To view the plan, simply prefix your query with the EXPLAIN keyword.

By optimizing your queries, you can reduce the amount of time it takes for your application to retrieve data from the database. This can improve the performance of your application and provide a better user experience. How to view the Query Execution Plan?

Why is it important?Understanding the query execution plan can help you optimize your SQL code and improve database performance. By examining the execution plan, you can identify areas for improvement, such as inefficient queries or missing indexes.

When you execute a query in a relational database, the database engine generates a query execution plan. This plan is a roadmap that the database uses to execute the query and retrieve the requested data.

Have you ever wondered how databases execute your queries?  As a developer working with data, understanding the query execution plan can be a powerful tool for optimizing your SQL code and improving database performance  What is a Query Execution Plan?
